Prince of Wales feather(s)
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Leptopteris</i>(formerly <i>Todea) superba</i>, crape fern, plume fern, ?king-fern., occas. Prince of Wales fern; an  ornamental New Zealand fern.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [1919 July 29] Ver.(WB). = Vernacular names used by settlers, supplied by W. Best, Otaki (And) <i>Leptopteris superba</i> W. Best (Otaki) Vernacular. (Andersen, 10 entries)
